# TailwindCSS 4+ Styling Guide

## TailwindCSS 4 Features
- Uses **CSS-based configuration** instead of JS config files
- Improved performance and DX

## className Patterns

### Single Classes
```tsx
<div className="flex items-center justify-center" />
```

### Multiple Classes with cn()
**Always wrap multiple classNames** with the [cn() function](mdc:app/lib/utils.ts):

```tsx
import { cn } from '@/lib/utils'

// ✅ Correct - using cn()
<div className={cn('base-class', 'another-class', className)} />

// ✅ Conditional classes with objects
<div className={cn({
  'text-red-500': hasError,
  'text-green-500': isSuccess,
  'opacity-50': isDisabled
})} />

// ✅ Complex combinations
<div className={cn(
  'flex items-center justify-center',
  'rounded-md border shadow-sm',
  {
    'bg-primary text-white': variant === 'primary',
    'bg-secondary': variant === 'secondary'
  },
  className
)} />
```

### Class Variance Authority (CVA)
For component variants, use CVA pattern like in [app/components/ui/button.tsx](mdc:app/components/ui/button.tsx):

```tsx
import { cva, type VariantProps } from 'class-variance-authority'

const variants = cva(
  "base classes",
  {
    variants: {
      variant: {
        default: 'variant classes',
        destructive: 'destructive classes'
      },
      size: {
        default: 'size classes',
        sm: 'small classes'
      }
    },
    defaultVariants: {
      variant: 'default',
      size: 'default'
    }
  }
)
```

## CSS File Structure
Modular CSS in [app/styles/](mdc:app/styles/):
- [app/styles/base.css](mdc:app/styles/base.css) - Base styles
- [app/styles/components.css](mdc:app/styles/components.css) - Component styles  
- [app/styles/theme.css](mdc:app/styles/theme.css) - Theme variables
- [app/app.css](mdc:app/app.css) - Main CSS importing others

## Theme Support
- Dark/Light mode with flash-less switching
- CSS custom properties for theming
- Use semantic color names (`gray-*`, `primary-*`, `secondary-*`, etc.)
